<subSubSection id="C362D9F0E80851357D6AFE353E63FE92" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="44" pageId="8" pageNumber="43" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE80851357D6AFE353E63FE92" blockId="8.[828,1436,481,536]" lastBlockId="9.[151,760,190,469]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="44" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E80851347D6AFE353CFFFE1F" bold="true" box="[828,958,481,504]" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">Comments.</emphasis>
This species was originally described based on material from 
<collectingRegion id="49BC4499E80851347DBAFDD53B7EFDFF" box="[1004,1087,513,536]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
, southwestern 
<collectingCountry id="F36FCAEBE80851347A80FDD53A56FDFF" box="[1238,1303,513,536]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">China</collectingCountry>
, andAttapeu and 
<collectingRegion id="49BC4499E80951357E95FF6A3E6DFF32" box="[195,300,190,213]" country="Laos" name="Viangchan" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Vientiane</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F36FCAEBE80951357F60FF6A3E2CFF32" box="[310,365,190,213]" name="Laos" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Laos</collectingCountry>
. Diagnostic characters of this species are oblique antennomeres 10 and 11 of the males, and large transverse expansion of the aedeagal parameres before the apices. The additional material examined extends the distributional range of 
<taxonomicName id="4C78F1F8E80951357F3AFEEA3E95FEB2" authorityName="Huang, Li &amp; Yin" authorityYear="2018" box="[364,468,318,341]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pselaphodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incisus">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E80951357F3AFEEA3E3DFEB2" box="[364,380,318,341]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90C5669E80951357FDCFEEA3E95FEB2" box="[394,468,318,341]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">incisus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<collectingRegion id="49BC4499E80951357FA0FEEA3DB5FEB2" box="[502,756,318,341]" country="Laos" name="Khammouan" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Ehammouane Province</collectingRegion>
, central 
<collectingCountry id="F36FCAEBE80951357EB0FE8A3E5CFE92" box="[230,285,350,373]" name="Laos" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Laos</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF07DAF3E80851347EC1F8023AC8F7F9" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037480" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5037480" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037480/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="43" startId="8.[151,182,2006,2025]" targetBox="[210,1383,586,1980]" targetPageId="8">
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE80851347EC1F8023AC8F7F9" blockId="8.[151,1437,2006,2078]" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">
Fig. 6. Male diagnostic features of 
<taxonomicName id="4C78F1F8E80851347F94F8023DCBF80E" authority="Yin &amp; Li, 2021" authorityName="Yin &amp; Li" authorityYear="2021" box="[450,650,2006,2025]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pselaphodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dalatensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E80851347F94F8023DCBF80E" box="[450,650,2006,2025]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">Pselaphodes dalatensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23FEB12E80851347CD9F8023D93F80E" box="[655,722,2006,2025]" pageId="8" pageNumber="43" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
A – eight antennal club, in ventral view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H–J – aedeagus, in dorsal (H), lateral (I), and ventral (J) view; E – apex of right paramere. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, E, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, H, I, J; 0.1 mm in E.
</paragraph>
</caption>
